StudyGoal: Evaluating respondents' use of provided clues to infer probable meanings of unfamiliar utterances?
comment: I was definitely confused by the clues, so I drew contradictory conclusions about the meanings of the response words "sha" and "bei". Seeing the mother smiling for "sha" and frowning for "bei", I imagined that they could mean "yes" and "no" respectively, but I thought the child's behavior seemed to contradict that? ... Then I imagined that the mother's responses could possibly be erroneous, if the mother (not knowing English) may have misunderstood the query words "truck" and "bucket". -- But if the query was about an attributive term in the mother's language (such as "zupi"), then the mother's affirmative or negative response would likely be accurate. ... I was probably overthinking all this, and only succeeded in confusing myself.
